The paper focuses on the application of person re-identification, which is a computer vision problem, and proposes a method to optimize deep representation learning using Singular Value Decomposition (SVD). Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also involves training a convolutional neural network (CNN) using a specific training scheme, which falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG). Additionally, the paper deals with matrix factorization and optimization, which are relevant to the categories of multimedia (cs.MM) and information retrieval (cs.IR). Finally, the paper proposes a novel method for deep learning, which can be categorized under artificial intelligence (cs.AI).
